data.name: m_lblSiteExampleHelp.Text
data.value: The site name is the portion of the URL starting after the protocol and before the path. Site names do not include port numbers.

data.name: m_lblStrongNameHelp.Text
data.value: The Strong Name membership condition is true for all assemblies with a strong name that matches the one defined below. Assemblies that meet this membership condition will be granted the permissions associated with this code group.

data.name: m_lblStrongName3Parts.Text
data.value: Provide the strong name's public key. The name and version are optional but provide a more secure condition.

data.name: m_lblCustomHelp.Text
data.value: This tool cannot create custom membership conditions. To incorporate a custom membership condition into the security policy, author it outside this tool in an XML file and import that file using the Import button.

data.name: m_lblSiteEntryHelp.Text
data.value: The URL must include the protocol such as 'ftp://' or 'http://'. An asterisk (*) can be used as a wildcard character at the end of the URL.

data.name: m_lblPublisherHelp.Text
data.value: The Publisher membership condition is true if an assembly is digitally signed with a certificate that matches the one below. Assemblies that meet this membership condition will be granted the permissions associated with this code group.

data.name: m_lblHashHelp.Text
data.value: The Hash membership condition is true for all assemblies with a hash that matches the algorithm below. Assemblies that meet this membership condition will be granted the permissions associated with this code group.

data.name: m_lblZoneHelp.Text
data.value: The Zone membership condition is true for all assemblies that originate from the zone listed below. Assemblies that meet this membership condition will be granted the permissions associated with this code group.

data.name: m_lblSiteHelp.Text
data.value: The Site membership condition is true for all assemblies that come from the site name below. Assemblies that meet this membership condition will be granted the permissions associated with this code group.

data.name: m_ImportHashHelp.Text
data.value: Use the Import button to retrieve the hash from an assembly based on the selected algorithm.

data.name: m_lblHashAlgo.Text
data.value: Choose the algorithm used to compute the assembly's hash:

data.name: m_lblMCHelp.Text
data.value: The membership condition specifies the condition that an assembly must meet in order to be a member of a code group.

data.name: m_lblURLHelp.Text
data.value: The URL membership condition is true for all assemblies that originate from the URL specified below. Assemblies that meet this membership condition will be granted the permissions associated with this code group.

data.name: m_lblSkipVerificationHelp.Text
data.value: The Skip Verification membership condition is true for all assemblies that request the right to skip verification. Assemblies that meet this membership condition will be granted the permissions associated with this code group.

data.name: m_lblImportStrongNameHelp.Text
data.value: Use the Import button to retrieve the strong name from an assembly.

data.name: m_lblAppDirectoryHelp.Text
data.value: The Application Directory membership condition is true for all assemblies in the same directory or in a child directory of the running application. Assemblies that meet this membership condition will be granted the permissions associated with this code group.

data.name: m_lblConditionType.Text
data.value: Choose the condition &type for this code group:

data.name: m_lblImportXMLHelp.Text
data.value: Use the Import button to import a custom membership condition from an existing XML file.

data.name: m_lblAllCodeDes.Text
data.value: The All Code membership condition is true for all assemblies that are evaluated against it. Assemblies that meet this membership condition will be granted the permissions associated with this code group.
